##############################################

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "parserImplicitPlane.pl",
  "PCCmacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);

##############################################

$a=random(2,9,1);
$b=random(1,10,1);
$ans2=random(2,15,1);
$c=$a*($ans2-$b);

Context("ImplicitPlane");
Context()->flags->set(showExtraParens=>0);
Context()->variables->are(x=>'Real');
Context()->flags->set(reduceConstants=>0);
$ans1 = ImplicitPlane("$a*(x-$b)= $c");

Context("LimitedNumeric");
$ans2 = Compute($ans2);

##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

Write an equation for the following situation, and then solve for the unknown. Please use [`x`] as the unknown variable.

    [@numberWord($c,capital=>1)@] is the product of [@numberWord($a)@] and [@numberWord($b)@] less than a number. What is the number?

Your equation is: 
    [_______________________]{$ans1->cmp(cmp_class => "a linear equation",correct_ans=>"$c=$a(x-$b)",correct_ans_latex_string=>"$c=$a(x-$b)")}

The unknown number is: 
    [___________]{$ans2}

END_PGML

##############################################

$s1=$b*$a;
$s2=$c+$s1;

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

Let the unknown number be [`x`]. 

Following "the product of", there are two expressions being multiplied: "[`[$a]`]" and "[`[$b]`] less than a number."

We need to use parentheses so that subtraction happens first.

The equation is:

    [`` [$c]=[$a](x-[$b]) ``]

Next, we solve for [`x`]:

    [`
\begin{aligned}
  [$c] &\;=\; [$a](x-[$b]) \\
  [$c] &\;=\; [$a]x-[$a] \cdot [$b]   \\
  [$c] &\;=\; [$a]x-[$s1]    \\
  [$c]\mathbf{{} +[$s1]} &\;=\; [$a]x-[$s1] \mathbf{{} +[$s1]} \\
  [$s2] &\;=\; [$a]x          \\
  \frac{[$s2]}{[$a]} &\;=\; \frac{[$a]x}{[$a]} \\
  [$ans2] &\;=\; x
\end{aligned}
`]

The unknown number is [`[$ans2]`].

END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();

